transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Six o'clock on Viagra, this is Jimmy, how can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yeah, Jimmy, I've had another withdrawal on my PayPal and I did not authorize and did not want to pay.

Speaker 1: Okay, let me see if I can pull you up and see what's going on.

Speaker 2: Is this Zack I'm speaking to?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Hi Zack, I see that you're getting the Viagra, the 50 mg.

Speaker 1: It looks like your prescription has you set up to get it every month.

Speaker 2: Is that too frequently for you or do you want to push it back another time?

Speaker 1: I tried the product and it did not work for me.

Speaker 2: I've had a vaccine that's been in me and I thought it might help, but it did not.

Speaker 1: So, I need your attention.

Speaker 2: Hey Zack, I'm looking at the, let me do this for you because, did you order online?

Speaker 1: I'm just curious.

Speaker 2: Did you order online?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Okay, and were you trying to get the Viagra, the ATB?

Speaker 1: That's what I got, yes.

Speaker 2: No, it looks like you got the regular Jened Viagra.

Speaker 1: So, let me get that fixed for you.

Speaker 2: Let me go ahead and send you out the correct one and basically I'm going to make sure that you try that and see how that will work for you.

Speaker 1: Okay, I'm going to make sure that the pharmacy sends you out the correct Viagra and I'm going to get that charge taken care of for you that you have out there.

Speaker 2: Okay?

Speaker 1: The first one they sent was the regular one?

Speaker 2: Yes, exactly.

Speaker 1: That's not what I ordered.

Speaker 2: Well, when you do it online, sometimes it can be a mix-up, but I'm going to get that sent out to you.

Speaker 1: Now, see you got the 50 mg.

Speaker 2: Can I increase it to the 100 mg?

Speaker 1: The 100 mg is probably more effective for you, too, rather than 50 mg?

Speaker 2: So, I'm going to get charged again?

Speaker 1: No, I'm going to send this out for you with no charge because the fact is that's what you should have got the first time, but I'm going to increase the mg from 50 to 100.

Speaker 2: Is that all right?

Speaker 1: Yes, that's fine.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Do not put me on a rotation of monthly to send it to me.

Speaker 2: I'm not going to do a monthly-monthly.

Speaker 1: I want you to try it.

Speaker 2: I'm going to postpone any order for like four months.

Speaker 1: I've got to give you more than enough time to try it.

Speaker 2: Okay?

Speaker 1: Right.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Now, I'll take care of that for you.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Not a problem.

Speaker 1: Take care.

Speaker 2: Bye.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye.
